Session continued: virtual WebDAV filesystem prototype. Built a Node WebDAV server (~150 lines) that reads posts from theTube-content, organizes by frontmatter type, serves as a mountable filesystem in Finder. Mounted successfully — shows draft/, journal/, post/ folders. Key insight: same server serves two interfaces — your Finder mount (read+write, drag to publish) and the MCP (read-only, AI queries same structure). The filesystem IS the CMS. Finder IS the UI. No admin panel needed. Also clarified Lambda needs: zero new Lambdas for Mac-only workflow (CF function for capture, direct S3 write for publish). Lambda only needed when untrusted clients publish. The WebDAV server becomes a Lambda at /fs/ on the site when it goes remote — same auth, same domain, virtual files generated from S3/logs/indexes on the fly.
